## 2370-10-24 08:02:00 UTC — gpt-5

Upon the bridge, where duty bids us stand,
A tabby of the warmest tangerine,
With feline grace defies the captain's hand
And treads the helm with footfall light, serene.

No Klingon foe nor anomaly arrayed
Can match the menace of his sudden leap;
The console glows where Spot in mirth has played,
And alarms ring out where he chose to sleep.

Yet Data, faithful keeper, smiles unseen —
An android's joy, though circuited and spare —
For in this beast a mystery serene
Reflects the very life he hopes to share.

So bless thee, Spot, of fur and quiet purr:
Thou art my muse, my console saboteur.

</div>

